The PAC led by newly elected president, Mzwanele Nyhontsho has visited the Kingdom of AmaXhosa at Nqadu Great Place in the Eastern Cape. The purpose was to introduce the new party leadership as the current leader comes from the same community. Nyhontsho says: “As you know that we are just coming from a national congress of the PAC and we have a new leadership, we have decided to go and visit the king of the Xhosas. Some of us, more especially the president of the PAC, comes from the land where the king is in charge.” “We just went there to pay a visit and salute to the king of the Xhosas.”